		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://lakefrontleakanddrain.com/?p=35</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>When Cleveland's winter wrath strikes and you suspect a frozen pipe, never use an open flame to thaw it, as this poses a severe fire risk and can damage your plumbing. Instead, safely apply gentle heat with a hairdryer or heating pad, and if you're unsure, always contact a local plumbing professional for assistance.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

